{"id":"byt-9mr","title":"Implement byt website sync command","description":"Add command to sync tool.toml files from workspace repos to website. Should:\n\n1. Read website repo path from [website] config section\n2. Walk workspace repos looking for tool.toml\n3. Parse and validate against schema (govnr/examples/tool.toml)\n4. Generate/update tool pages in website repo (config: toolz_dir)\n5. Update toolz/index.js with tools array\n6. Copy media files (icon, screenshot) to public/ (config: public_dir)\n7. Be idempotent - only update if content changed\n8. Support --commit flag to auto-commit changes\n9. Support localized fields (tagline_de, description_de, etc.)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-01T15:03:31.648518450Z","updated_at":"2026-01-01T15:13:25.562805438Z","closed_at":"2026-01-01T15:13:25.562805438Z"}
{"id":"byt-a33","title":"byt memory should auto-detect repo from cwd git remote, not just catalog","description":"When running 'byt memory add' from ~/byteowlz/octo, it says 'At workspace root or outside workspace, using govnr store' even though octo is a valid git repo in the byteowlz workspace. byt should: 1) Check if cwd is inside a git repo, 2) Extract repo name from git remote or directory name, 3) Use that as the store name (creating if needed). Currently it only checks the catalog, which may not be up to date.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-30T09:41:41.205905542Z","updated_at":"2025-12-30T09:41:41.205905542Z"}
