{"id":"byt-smr6","title":"bytdesign-system sync: vendored distribute-down command (mirror templates/schema)","description":"## STATUS: IMPLEMENTED + VERIFIED ✅ (2026-06-25)\n\nAlready implemented in commit `da0ac89 feat: added byt style repo feature`\n(landed before this issue was filed). Verified end-to-end against the real\nsource repo:\n\n- `byt design-system sync --repo oqto_refactor` → fetches `byteowlz/design-system@v0.1.0`\n  via shallow `git fetch --depth 1`, lands `impls/shadcn-ts/` src into the\n  configured path. DRY-RUN honored.\n- **D1 confirmed:** syncs `src/` only — `dist/` and `node_modules/` correctly\n  absent (dist is gitignored build artifact).\n- **D2 / the stamp confirmed:** writes `VENDORED.md` with source url, impl,\n  ref, full sha, sync timestamp, byt version, AND a tree fingerprint.\n- **Drift detection proven both directions:**\n  - `status` → `[behind (pinned v0.1.0 -> latest v0.1.0)]` when upstream advances\n  - `status` → `[diverged (local edits since sync; pinned v0.1.0)]` when locals\n    edit (caught a simulated tamper; resync restored it)\n- Command surface matches spec exactly: `sync` / `status` / `list`,\n  `--repo` / `--ref` / `--build` flags, global `--dry-run`.\n- Config model matches spec: global `DesignSystemConfig` defaults +\n  per-consumer `design-system.toml` manifest (source/ref/impl/path/build_cmd).\n\nDesign-system repo tagged `v0.1.0` (first pinned ref). oqto manifest at\n`oqto_refactor/design-system.toml` consuming it.\n\n## Two minor follow-ups (non-blocking, defer)\n\n1. **`status` display edge case:** shows `[behind (pinned v0.1.0 -> latest v0.1.0)]`\n   even when pinned==latest (the \"behind\" label fires whenever a latest tag\n   exists, regardless of equality). Should show `[up-to-date]` when\n   pinned-sha == latest-tag-sha.\n2. **`--repo` filter uses exact catalog key:** must pass `oqto_refactor`, not\n   `oqto`. Consider fuzzy/case-insensitive matching or a clearer error\n   (\"did you mean...\") since the dir-vs-catalog-name mismatch is a natural trap.\n\n## Original spec (retained for reference)\n\n[see Why / Command surface / Config block / sync behavior / status behavior /\nTwo decisions / Non-goals / Acceptance in git history]\n\n## Acceptance recheck\n\n- [x] `byt design-system sync` lands `impls/shadcn-ts/` src into a configured\n      consumer path, stamped with origin/ref/sha/date.\n- [x] `status` reports drift vs latest source tag (both behind + diverged).\n- [x] Works against `byteowlz/design-system` ref `v0.1.0`.\n- [x] Mirrors the config + handler + enum wiring style of `schema`/`templates`.\n- [x] `--dry-run` honored.\n- [ ] AGENTS.md command table updated (follow-up — design-system not yet in byt's AGENTS.md command table).","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-06-23T18:11:28.998681067Z","updated_at":"2026-06-25T06:57:57.089183505Z","sessions":["019ed978-f0ec-7ee4-bdab-98077b5ce09b"]}
